# Claude Code Hooks Installer — Verification Checklist

## Pre-Installation
- [ ] Python 3.6+ installed: python3 --version
- [ ] ~/.claude directory exists: ls -la ~/.claude/
- [ ] Writable permissions: touch ~/.claude/test && rm ~/.claude/test

## Installation
- [ ] Run install.py: python3 install.py
- [ ] Choose hook packs (Safety/Quality/Productivity)
- [ ] Installation completes without errors

## Post-Installation Verification
- [ ] ~/.claude/hooks/ directory created
- [ ] 6 hook scripts exist (if --all installed)
- [ ] Hook scripts have executable permissions: ls -la ~/.claude/hooks/
- [ ] ~/.claude/settings.json created with hooks section
- [ ] settings.json is valid JSON: python3 -m json.tool ~/.claude/settings.json

## Test Hooks
- [ ] Safety — Try running: rm -rf / (should be blocked)
- [ ] Quality — Edit large file (>100 lines, should warn)
- [ ] Productivity — Edit 6+ files (should remind to commit)

## Cleanup (Optional)
- [ ] Review settings.json and disable unnecessary hooks
- [ ] Remove duplicate entries if re-running installer
- [ ] Delete old settings.backup_*.json if space constrained

## Done!
- [ ] All hooks working as expected
- [ ] No errors in Claude Code output
- [ ] Ready for production use
